e it, but they can roll on the RBB and there is no ac on this item...just 15wis/int. However, SKs fearkitting, pallies healing, and rangers hate kitting etc would all benifit from this.<br><br><br>so lets talk about it....post here with thoughts / opinions<br><br><br><br>Quichan Paine<br>Leader of the Niasa en'Valrim<br>monk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/useanchanactiveworlds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seanchan ActiveWorlds</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/19/02 10:18:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1358.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox loot debat: eyepatch</span><hr size=1> Quichan,<br><br>I'm glad you raised this question, for it actually has an impact far beyond just the eyepatch. Over and over you can read forums and opinions on Allakhazam and other places about which loot is best for which classes. And like all issues of controversy, you will hear a myriad of views, many diametrically opposed to each other. When I visit Allakhazam or Everlore or some class forum to research an item, I usually see the majority of postings arguing about which class is best suited for which item.<br><br>Well, here is my two bits, knowing that many will disagree.<br><br>I feel we should use the Class and Race listings that Verant has coded onto the items, to decide who qualifies for a random. If an item is All/All, then let every raid member participate on the random if they so choose. If we actually used Verant's coding as our guide, the vast majority of arguments and counter-arguments and controversy during and after raids, concerning loot rights, would be eliminated. If some dissenter began to whine and moan, you could simply point them to the Class/Race coding on the item and tell them to shut-up or leave. As long as each and every item is debated by players and then through popular consent certain qualifying classes or races are excluded, there will always be problems in loot distribution.<br><br>Oh yes, one last comment. Assuming we use the Class/Race listing from Verant to qualify players for randoms, and the winner of an item is someone who is less able to use it than some other class or race (again that is often a subjective determination), then let those who want to trade or bid for the item do so. I am not saying the winner should go immediately to the EC tunnel and offer it in auction. What I am saying is those people on the specific raid should feel free to offer trades or coin for the item if the winner agrees to deal.<br><br>OK, now I am bracing myself for the full barrage of dissenters. The can of worms is now open, let's have a good old fashion debate.<br><br> <p><p><img src="http://www.eqicon.com/graphics/ICoN_sean.jpg" width="180" height="140">   <br>  <font color="#FF0033"><b><a href="mailto:seanchans@yahoo.com">Seanchans</a><br>  54 Shaman and Guild Leader, <a href="http://www.eqicon.com">Inner Circle of   Norrath</a><br>  Erollisi Marr Server<br>And holder of the Spear of Fate<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126765">Inspect Me if You Really Must</a></b></font><br>  <b><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" color="#FF0033"><i>"A few people   working together to build a better future"</i></font></b> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uheliuswallace.sh