e the wiz or cleric in your group able to cast an extra 2kdmg or comp heal, or would you rather the ranger gets off a small heal or snare? i think wis/int casters benefit from this item much more then hybrids.<br><br>again, you wouldnt have any melee show up if casters could roll on rbb, same as no casters show up if melee could roll on patch. up to the leader how he wants to run his raids, but most of the time it cant be done without both types being there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uheliuswallace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>helius wallace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 725<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/21/02 9:05:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1358.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox loot debat: eyepatch</span><hr size=1> Just crossed my mind. . .<br><br>What if everything besides epic loot was made FFA?<br><br>RBB and Eyepatch drops, anyone who wants either can roll.<br><br>Personally, I would never do a Vox raid like that, but who knows. . . someone may. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umindadar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindadar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/22/02 6:00:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1358.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Power multipliers</span><hr size=1> I agree that there are circumstances where added mana from wis/int is desired for hybrids. I'm sure everyone can agree on that.<br><br>I also believe and agree that there are many more circumstances where added mana is desired for pure casters. I'm also sure that everyone will agree with that.<br><br>Taking into account how much &quot;power&quot; that character will gain from acquiring an item has always been the determining factor in distributing loot. Thus why most will distribute the eyepatch to casters and RBBs to melee.<br><br>I agree with the fact that Verant is not stupid in determining the class/race restrictions (well, sometimes they are, but they fix the moronic ones). After all, if you wanted to max the wis/int of your warrior (for some reason), what would you use? They keep a lot of these items open like the eyepatch for freedom of choice in how you want your char to be equipped. I'm sure there's some ogre/troll warrior smiths out there that have bought an eyepatch for obvious reasons.<br><br>Now, a hybrid will gain some power from the use of the eyepatch, there's no denying that. Pure casters also gain some power from the eyepatch, and again, there's no denying that. The main argument is from whom would gain the most power. Those that gain the most power will benefit most, and thus benefit the greater good as well (thus why most guilds use NBG). The &quot;greater good&quot; does not exist for pickup raids, so NBG is restricted to those (classes) that will gain the most power.<br><br>I'd say that when comparing the power-gained from a hybrid as compaired to a caster is about a 1:3 or 1:4 ratio (meaning a pure caster gets 3 or 4 times as much improvement from the item as compaired to a hybrid). For a pure melee, the ratio would be much more in favor of the pure caster. I'm leaning toward 4 in my mind, so I'll go with that for now...<br><br>Now, to be fair to all that attend, if they can use, they should have a chance to roll for it. If the character plans on rolling for that item, and the item is one that is not normally awarded to that class, it must be considered by the leader according to some guidelines. First, the character wishing this must announce his/her intention to the leader and any officers that he/she may have helping. Second, the character gives up all rights to roll on other loot. Third, it is announced to the rest of the raid the intentions for special rolls during the time allotted for strategic discussion (in chat or elsewhere), but done before the loot may drop. Finally, the rolls are done according to the power multipliers that are associated with each item. This means that if a ranger1, wiz1, wiz2, and necro1 wanted to roll on the eyepatch, the roll would look like this: ranger1=1, wiz1=2-5, wiz2=6-9, necro1=10-13 (assuming the power mulitplier is 1:4 for hybrid:caster for the eyepatch).<br><br>Now some will argue that giving up other loot for a chance as low as shown above is unfair. It is not unless you are greedy. Unfortunately, EQ is a very greedy game, so that's not a good reason. If you are a magician with a white dragonscale cloak and particpate in a vox raid, most likely you only want the eyepatch. Also, if you are a ranger with epics and a better belt than an RBB and you have no real reason to attend a vox raid (but an eyepatch may be nice for that ghetto kiting and your fletching), then you might attend because it can increase your power even in a slight way. Now, the ranger can sell that eyepatch for a good chunk of $$ and could possibly buy something better for himself. If this magician and ranger rolled evenly, and the ranger assumes the magician will use, and the magician assumes the ranger will either use seldomly or sell, it's not fair for the ranger to roll evenly again the magician.<br><br>IMO, for no drop items, giving up the right to roll on other items should be waved, because there's no change for selling. Thus, if the eyepatch was no drop, the ranger could roll on whatever else drops that he wishes.<br><br>After playing a hybrid and pure caster in the high levels, this is my humble opinion.<br><br>Mindadar (retired and sold)<br>Queylon<br>Tweedledoo<br><br>United Independent <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=1358.topic&start=21&stop=29>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=1358.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=1358.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1358.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=1358.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.threadControl?topicID=1358.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1358.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1358.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub4.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="emarrmessageboardrules">Message Board Rules<option value="emarrlinks">Links<option val